ine than succeed.  While my raw rate has risen to roughly one-in-three, I go through spells of 4-5-6 combines without a make.; and my sample size is still much, much too small to give you a REAL indicator of the overall make rate at my skill.  I currently pay 500pp each for Haze Panther Eye, and 200ish for Diamonds (normal, not blue).  I'm willing to trade 6 (eye + diamond) sets for a GVD - which, for those of you interested in a GVD and good at math...  ...is a bargain.  Of course, try hunting Haze Panthers for a couple hours first :)<br><br>3) Other info?  Sure.  The GVD is purely a device of conveniece.  There are those who think it's a fantastic waste of money.  In short, you pay roughly the same for GVD charges as you do for potions... ...and the ONLY advantage the GVD has over potions (other than the coolness factor) is that batteries STACK.<br><br>I currently charge 9k for a GVD &quot;kit&quot; which inclues a toolbox and a 1k stack of batteries (or 105 total charges).  I also sell them more regularly &quot;bare&quot; for 8k.  I have them in-stock now on a mule in commons (although he's going to move to Bazaar fairly soon).<br><br>I suggest you ask someone who has one how they value theirs.  I've yet to have a dissatisfied customer. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>, Guildleader <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uehrnam.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ehrnam</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(2/12/02 9:22:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1753.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Palimax - Tinker